[97mDESCRIPTION
        hostname[37m is a simple command-line utility used to show or set the hostname of the Monolith system.

        If [95mname[37m is specified, and the executing user has the proper permissions, the system hostname will be set. If [95mname[37m is specified, but the current user does not have the proper permissions, [97mhostname[37m will throw an error. If [95mname[37m is not specified, the system hostname will be printed to standard output.

[97mEXAMPLES
        hostname[37m
            Displays the system's hostname.

        [97mhostname [95mmono[37m
            Sets the system's hostname to [95mmono[37m.

